President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday held a closed-door meeting with Governor Aminu Masari of Katsina State. Masari went to the villa few hours after news broke that the president had tested negative to the coronavirus (COVID-19). The president also held another meeting with the security chiefs, including the National Security Adviser, Major General Babagana Monguno (rtd.); Director-General, Department of State Services (DSS), Yusuf Bichi; and the Inspector-General of Police, Mohammed Adamu. Members of Presidential Task Force on Covid-19 were also sighted at State House, Abuja yesterday. Buhari meets security chiefs as coronavirus spreads in Nigeria President Buhari celebrates Sallah in Daura, receives Masari, Ganduje, others N/west, N/central close schools, Lagos bans religious gatherings